#It is noted that:
#most sightings of Cuculus canorus are concentrated in the ‘Cool Temperate Moist’ regions
#this same climatic region also has a significant population of Prunella modularis and Acrocephalus scirpaceus
#the cuckoo is much less common in drier and warmer regions.

